    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-11-13T12:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-11-13T12:42:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <head>378. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the European
                        Communities</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d378fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, INCO–WOOL 17 US. Limited Official Use; Priority. Repeated to Bonn,
                        The Hague, Luxembourg, Paris for <gloss target="#t_USOECD1">USOECD</gloss>,
                        Rome, and Geneva for <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Brussels</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-11-13T17:42:00+00:00">November 13, 1968,
                        1742Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10499. Subject: Commission Note Verbale on wool fabric bill (<gloss
                        target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 90–638).</p>
                <pb facs="0911" n="877" xml:id="pg_877"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>There follows informal Mission translation of Note Verbale received today
                        from the Directorate General for External Trade.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Directorate General for External Trade presents its compliments to the
                        United States Mission and wishes to inform it of the concern and
                        disappointment experienced by the Community over the promulgation in the
                        United States on Oct. 26 of a law amending the general rule for tariff
                        classification of certain fabrics containing wool. It recalls that the
                        attention of the American Government had already been called to the damage
                        which such a measure would cause to community export interests and to the
                        balance of concessions resulting from the Kennedy Round negotiations.</item>
                </list>
                <p>It regrets that the considerations furnished in support of these representations
                    could not be taken into consideration in order to avoid creating such damage.
                    The Community, faced by the situation created by the promulgation in the law in
                    question, will be obliged to protect its interests at the appropriate time in
                    the framework of <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Complimentary closing, dated November 13, Brussels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJR3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Schaetzel</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
